Here is a different interpretation of this story.

Is Touka going to eat Ma-Kun?
NO. There is a LOT of evidence that Touka (the female Man-Eating Demi-Human (MEDH)) is NOT regularly eating humans.
A Man-Eating animal just means that they WILL eat humans, NOT that they regularly do so.
Female mantis insects are known for eating after sex, usually the male brings a "tribute" animal for the female to eat, otherwise she may try eating him.
MEDH males bring tribute to females (dinner dates). Most likely they bring small animals like cats or dogs. Ma-Kun is offered as the FOURTH tribute by a male MEDH, the male would likely bring increasing larger tributes, so a human is the largest he has brought. She reacts violently to his offering striking him and insulting him saying he only brings easy prey. She thus made it 'very clear' that humans are NOT a good tribute.
In this world, man has conquered the Demi-humans and imposed his laws on them (page 14), so angering the humans is something Demi-H

So there's a few people debating/giving their two cents on this insect lady and her motives/true intentions. 

Personally, I'm in the "He won't get eaten" camp due to some of the points laid down by dimyell and randomdude. In addition to what they've said, I'd like to draw attention to much earlier in the story - when he first interacts with her after the initial kidnapping. He mentions that his family is likely worried about him, which leads to a panel of her face in (what I assume is meant to be) somber, slightly sad lighting in which she remarks that "humans actually have families". This in conjunction with her motherly (and clearly possessive-ish) behavior and the fact she's apparently done this before makes me believe she does want a genuine 'family' of sorts, and is attempting (and has attempted) to forcibly create one out of tributes brought to her. Just my thoughts, though.
